03/07/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- An army rapid intervention unit will become fully professional by the end of this year, in line with plans to modernise the armed forces, Defence Minister Fatmir Meidiu announced on Saturday (1 July). 
He was speaking to reporters during his visit to the Zall-Herr base near Tirana, where the 2nd Rapid Intervention Brigade battalion is located. 
He noted that in January, professional soldiers made up only 6.5 per cent of the unit, while in June, they represented 65 per cent. 
(Albanian News - 03/07/06)
